div.div: Intellij comment shortcut opens help tab on the Mac menu bar
Remove or replace the Cmd + Shift + / shortcut in your mac. Apple menu-> System Preferences-> Keyboard -> Shortcuts.
mongodb status of index creation job

At the mongo shell, type below command to see the current progress: rs0:PRIMARY> db.currentOp(true).inprog.forEach(function(op){ if(op.msg!==undefined) print(op.msg) })

Kubectl command to list pods of a deployment in Kubernetes

Is there a way to use kubectl to list only the pods belonging to a deployment? Currently, I do this to get pods: kubectl get pods| grep hello But it seems an overkill to get ALL the pods when I am interested to know only the pods for a given deployment. I use the output of this command to see the status of all pods, and then possibly exec into one of them. I also tried kc get -o wide deployments hellodeployment, but it does not print the Pod names.
IntelliJ PlantUML plugin does not detect *.pu files

I installed the PlantUML plugin in IntelliJ Ultimate 2020.2. I have a repo with a bunch of *.pu files, but these are not being rendered. However if I change the file extension to *.puml it works. Is there a way to configure the plugin so that it can read *.pu files as well?
